04/06/2004
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- A two-day conference of women parliamentarians from Southeast Europe opened in Skopje on Thursday (3 June). The event is focusing on legislative efforts against human trafficking and discrimination. Participants will also discuss women in the media.
In other news, Macedonia's new interior minister, Siljian Avramovski, is vowing to intensify police reforms and focus on strategic priorities, including the fight against organised crime. He held his first official meeting with EU Special Representative to Skopje Soren Jessen-Petersen on Thursday. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 04/06/04; Makfax, A1 TV - 03/06/04)
